1
00:00:49,080 --> 00:00:54,926
(music)A faithless lover's kiss

2
00:00:55,031 --> 00:01:00,048
(music)Is written on the wind

3
00:01:00,148 --> 00:01:05,481
(music)A night of stolen bliss

4
00:01:05,587 --> 00:01:07,790
(music)Is written

5
00:01:07,890 --> 00:01:11,150
(music) On the wind

6
00:01:11,249 --> 00:01:16,550
(music)Just like the dying leaves

7
00:01:16,654 --> 00:01:20,515
(music) Our dreams we've calmly

8
00:01:20,621 --> 00:01:23,468
(music) Thrown away

9
00:01:23,564 --> 00:01:29,126
(music)Now they've blown away

10
00:01:29,225 --> 00:01:32,966
(music)Softly flown away

11
00:01:33,064 --> 00:01:37,732
(music) The promises we made

12
00:01:37,830 --> 00:01:42,945
(music) Our whispers in the breeze

13
00:01:43,044 --> 00:01:48,280
(music) They echo and they fade

14
00:01:48,386 --> 00:01:53,752
(music)Just like our memories

15
00:01:53,856 --> 00:01:57,270
(music) Though you are gone

16
00:01:57,375 --> 00:01:59,676
(music)From me

17
00:01:59,774 --> 00:02:04,028
(music) We never can really be

18
00:02:04,125 --> 00:02:06,361
(music)Apart

19
00:02:06,459 --> 00:02:10,419
(music) What's written on the wind

20
00:02:10,522 --> 00:02:16,019
(music)Is written in my heart

21
00:02:16,120 --> 00:02:17,942
[Wind Howling]

22
00:02:25,652 --> 00:02:27,474
[Gunshot]

23
00:03:45,398 --> 00:03:47,852
Hello

24
00:03:47,958 --> 00:03:51,502
- What happened to Mrs. Black?
- My predecessor? She was paroled

25
00:03:51,604 --> 00:03:53,873
So you're the new
executive secretary, huh?

26
00:03:53,971 --> 00:03:57,516
Don't let that title deceive you
I do everything but wipe windshields

27
00:03:57,618 --> 00:03:59,984
- I'm Mitch Wayne
- Yes, I recognized you

28
00:04:00,081 --> 00:04:03,309
- I'm Lucy Moore
- Recognized me? From where?

29
00:04:03,408 --> 00:04:05,546
Oh, come now
Surely you realize

30
00:04:05,647 --> 00:04:08,134
how often your photograph
has graced our tabloids?

31
00:04:08,238 --> 00:04:13,058
But the captions usually read,
"Kyle Hadley, Prince Charming
of the oil empire, and friend"

32
00:04:13,165 --> 00:04:15,749
The dashing Kyle Hadley

33
00:04:15,852 --> 00:04:17,956
I saw him dash through
the office recently

34
00:04:18,059 --> 00:04:20,130
Seems he misplaced
his money belt

35
00:04:20,234 --> 00:04:24,705
- Again?
- A hat was passed,
and I contributed $1647

36
00:04:24,808 --> 00:04:28,189
Well, for that, you ought to get
an oil well named after you

37
00:04:28,295 --> 00:04:31,774
- Your boss in?
- No, Mr. Ryan's out of town

38
00:04:31,877 --> 00:04:34,844
- I guess you'll have
to pinch-hit for him
- What can I do for you?

39
00:04:34,948 --> 00:04:38,143
Kyle Hadley's at 21,
in the mood for a conference

40
00:04:38,243 --> 00:04:42,300
- Business, of course
- Look, I'm only Mr. Ryan's secretary

41
00:04:42,402 --> 00:04:46,045
- I don't think it'd be proper to...
- Would you rather wipe windshields?

42
00:04:47,775 --> 00:04:49,597
All right

43
00:04:50,783 --> 00:04:53,084
Kyle and I flew in
from Texas this afternoon

44
00:04:53,182 --> 00:04:55,733
- Sounds urgent
- Very

45
00:04:55,836 --> 00:04:59,064
- Kyle said he felt
like a steak sandwich
- Steak sandwich?

46
00:04:59,163 --> 00:05:01,529
And who serves the best
steak sandwich in the world?

47
00:05:01,626 --> 00:05:04,210
- 21?
- Simple, isn't it?

48
00:05:05,689 --> 00:05:07,510
Or should I say
simpleminded?

49
00:05:08,919 --> 00:05:11,155
1,380 miles for a...

50
00:05:12,854 --> 00:05:16,976
- Then you were fooling me
about a business conference
- No, that was my idea,

51
00:05:17,076 --> 00:05:20,784
you know, in case
Mr. Jasper Hadley should ask
why we came to town

52
00:05:20,883 --> 00:05:23,882
Oh, the big boss Well...

53
00:05:23,986 --> 00:05:26,855
Cheer up You might
get your picture in the paper

54
00:05:26,961 --> 00:05:29,033
Is that all you live for?

55
00:05:30,192 --> 00:05:34,282
- Guess again, Miss Moore
- I'm sorry

56
00:05:34,382 --> 00:05:37,643
I just wanted you to understand
how I feel about such things

57
00:05:38,925 --> 00:05:40,746
- Know something?
- What?

58
00:05:40,844 --> 00:05:42,666
Maybe we're two of a kind

59
00:05:47,337 --> 00:05:49,377
Harry, put it on my tab

60
00:05:49,417 --> 00:05:52,263
- Of course, Mr. Hadley
- Who's this friend we're waiting for?

61
00:05:52,360 --> 00:05:55,042
Mitch Wayne, my sidekick

62
00:05:55,143 --> 00:05:57,379
Mmm, where do his millions
come from?

63
00:05:57,478 --> 00:05:59,713
He's eccentric...
he's poor

64
00:05:59,813 --> 00:06:03,227
- [Chuckles] I'll bet
- Honey, you would lose

65
00:06:03,331 --> 00:06:08,032
Mitch is just a country boy
The kind of assets he's got
you can't buy with money

66
00:06:10,464 --> 00:06:13,016
Sorry, kids
I'll have to make this
some other time

67
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:16,980
- He's not eccentric
- No, he's as rich as Rockefeller

68
00:06:17,086 --> 00:06:19,932
- Hello, I'm Kyle Hadley
- I'm Lucy Moore

69
00:06:20,029 --> 00:06:23,323
Lucy Moore
Your taste is improving

70
00:06:23,420 --> 00:06:26,266
Miss Moore is Bill Ryan's
new executive secretary

71
00:06:26,363 --> 00:06:29,526
A member of the happy, happy
Hadley Industrial family

72
00:06:31,449 --> 00:06:33,270
This is sure cozy

73
00:06:40,598 --> 00:06:44,491
There are rare moments
when only champagne will do
This is one of them

74
00:06:46,227 --> 00:06:49,008
Like the lyrics say,
"Are you from Dixie or where?"

75
00:06:49,106 --> 00:06:51,723
Indiana Small town
you probably never heard of

76
00:06:51,825 --> 00:06:53,897
Anytime you ask me,
I'll put it on the map

77
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:56,236
What shows
in your crystal ball?

78
00:06:56,336 --> 00:06:59,498
Oh, I'll probably walk down an aisle
and wind up in a suburb

79
00:06:59,599 --> 00:07:02,893
- with a husband,
mortgage and children
- That's not for you

80
00:07:02,989 --> 00:07:06,370
- Why not?
- Got too much beauty and brains
to fall into a trap like that

81
00:07:06,476 --> 00:07:08,744
Just what sort of trap
do you suggest?

82
00:07:08,843 --> 00:07:12,551
How would you like to join
the Kyle Hadley Society
for the Prevention of Boredom?

83
00:07:12,650 --> 00:07:15,812
- [Chuckles]
What would my duties be?
- Not duties

84
00:07:15,912 --> 00:07:19,653
Pleasures, such as Kyle Hadley's
guided tour through the gossip columns,

85
00:07:19,751 --> 00:07:21,823
around the world
in 80 headlines

86
00:07:21,925 --> 00:07:25,633
- I'm afraid that'd bore me
- What wouldn't bore you?

87
00:07:25,732 --> 00:07:27,554
My career... advertising

88
00:07:27,652 --> 00:07:30,368
Bravo...
as they say in Texas

89
00:07:32,002 --> 00:07:35,001
- Where did you learn
the advertising game?
- With the Sheraton Agency

90
00:07:35,105 --> 00:07:37,657
- Top drawer?
- One of Madison Avenue's finest

91
00:07:37,760 --> 00:07:39,582
Good enough

92
00:07:39,679 --> 00:07:41,501
I'll buy you the agency

93
00:07:43,166 --> 00:07:45,500
What if I took you up on that?

94
00:07:45,597 --> 00:07:47,735
[Snaps Fingers]
A phone, please

95
00:07:47,836 --> 00:07:49,658
[Man]
Yes, Mr. Hadley

96
00:07:49,755 --> 00:07:53,910
- You're really serious, aren't you?
- Sure I am

97
00:07:54,010 --> 00:07:56,856
- What's the number?
- The agency or my apartment?

98
00:07:56,953 --> 00:08:00,018
- Seriously...
- Very seriously, forget it

99
00:08:02,072 --> 00:08:05,780
I'm only following the advice
of a Texas philosopher who said,
"Give the little girl a big..."

100
00:08:05,878 --> 00:08:09,968
I think it's time we heard from
another county What do you do
for the Hadley Oil Company?

101
00:08:10,068 --> 00:08:13,133
We're troubleshooters
Wherever they want trouble,
they send for us

102
00:08:15,122 --> 00:08:17,772
I, uh, have a sheepskin
that says I'm a geologist

103
00:08:17,874 --> 00:08:20,808
- That adds up
- I was kicked out
of the same school

104
00:08:20,913 --> 00:08:23,431
They found rocks
in my head

105
00:08:23,535 --> 00:08:25,803
Shouldn't you be going back
to the office?

106
00:08:25,902 --> 00:08:27,789
Apparently,
I never should have left

107
00:08:27,886 --> 00:08:31,626
- We haven't finished
our champagne
- Remarkable, isn't it?

108
00:08:39,113 --> 00:08:41,414
I think we need cigarettes
Get a carton

109
00:08:41,512 --> 00:08:43,650
We'll get a cab, meanwhile

110
00:08:43,751 --> 00:08:45,573
Thank you, Mr. Hadley

111
00:08:47,974 --> 00:08:49,948
Carton of Mullhall, please

112
00:08:53,316 --> 00:08:55,137
Thank you

113
00:09:02,817 --> 00:09:05,150
[Taxi Departs]

114
00:09:05,248 --> 00:09:07,898
Don't look now,
but you've dropped your friend

115
00:09:07,998 --> 00:09:11,641
You advertising people...
so clever with words

116
00:09:15,196 --> 00:09:17,268
Guess I've fallen
from your grace

117
00:09:17,372 --> 00:09:19,193
Does it really matter?

118
00:09:20,890 --> 00:09:22,831
Change your course
Teterborough Airport

119
00:09:22,938 --> 00:09:26,352
Look, if you don't mind,
I'd like to get off
the merry-go-round

120
00:09:26,456 --> 00:09:28,627
I can't quit now

121
00:09:28,727 --> 00:09:31,377
I want you to meet
another fellow... a real one

122
00:09:32,598 --> 00:09:34,865
- Some other time, perhaps
- Some times, like now,

123
00:09:34,964 --> 00:09:37,134
I can get you
in the terminal

124
00:09:37,235 --> 00:09:39,470
I want us to be friends
when we say good-bye

125
00:09:39,570 --> 00:09:41,642
Well, then let me
give you a tip

126
00:09:41,745 --> 00:09:46,119
- Drop me at the office
- And if I do, I lose you

127
00:09:48,175 --> 00:09:51,687
Look, Lucy, once we're up in the blue,
I'm a different fellow...

128
00:09:51,790 --> 00:09:54,374
a lot different
from this character

129
00:09:56,652 --> 00:09:59,717
All right
Maybe I should meet him

130
00:10:04,425 --> 00:10:07,010
No stunts now, like buzzing
the Empire State Building

131
00:10:07,081 --> 00:10:09,022
The only stunts I do
are in nightclubs

132
00:10:09,128 --> 00:10:10,949
May I ask why?

133
00:10:11,047 --> 00:10:13,828
I wouldn't admit this
to anyone but you,

134
00:10:13,926 --> 00:10:15,748
but I drink too much

135
00:10:28,897 --> 00:10:32,638
- Here's your change
- Can't shake you, can I?

136
00:10:32,736 --> 00:10:34,557
Goes both ways

137
00:10:38,205 --> 00:10:40,921
Am I safe in this crate?

138
00:10:41,021 --> 00:10:45,142
I guess so
The tanks are loaded, and
the pilot isn't, for a change

139
00:10:45,242 --> 00:10:47,063
Lucy

140
00:11:05,971 --> 00:11:09,003
You know, I've seen you before
at the office

141
00:11:09,106 --> 00:11:12,007
- A fleeting glance, wasn't it?
- How much did you contribute?

142
00:11:12,112 --> 00:11:15,111
Enough
How long have you known Mitch?

143
00:11:15,216 --> 00:11:17,670
My dad introduced us
when we started the first grade

144
00:11:17,774 --> 00:11:21,668
- That must have been
before your father struck oil
- Dad was worth 100 million then

145
00:11:21,773 --> 00:11:26,114
He had no use for private
schools, and he wanted me
to grow up with Mitch

146
00:11:26,219 --> 00:11:28,455
Why Mitch in particular?

147
00:11:28,554 --> 00:11:32,295
Mitch's old man
is my dad's boyhood pal...
his idol, I guess

148
00:11:32,393 --> 00:11:34,977
A small rancher...
kind of a legend in our county

149
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:37,861
Great hunter, sort of
a throwback to Daniel Boone

150
00:11:39,334 --> 00:11:42,203
I used to wish
he was my father

151
00:11:44,037 --> 00:11:46,589
Is your father aware of this?

152
00:11:46,692 --> 00:11:51,960
Dad's a big man... so big
that he and I know I can't fit
his shoes, or even come close

153
00:11:52,066 --> 00:11:54,814
- Can anybody?
- Yes

154
00:11:54,912 --> 00:11:56,766
Mitch

155
00:12:05,628 --> 00:12:08,180
When I was kicked out of college,
Dad gave up hoping

156
00:12:08,283 --> 00:12:11,381
Mitch's qualities
might rub off on me

157
00:12:11,482 --> 00:12:15,158
It's easy to talk like this
when you're 6,000 feet above
the big poker table

158
00:12:15,257 --> 00:12:19,052
- Poker table?
- Sure The big one...
from Maine to California

159
00:12:20,247 --> 00:12:22,351
Down there, I'm a guy
with too many chips

160
00:12:22,454 --> 00:12:26,511
I throw 'em up in the air,
and a few land on my shoulders

161
00:12:26,613 --> 00:12:30,670
They'd be disappointed if
I didn't behave like a playboy...
didn't end up like my uncle

162
00:12:30,771 --> 00:12:33,553
- How did he end up?
- Joe Hadley?

163
00:12:33,650 --> 00:12:35,472
Lived hard and he died hard

164
00:12:35,570 --> 00:12:38,765
He survived a few duels
over some European duchesses
and countesses,

165
00:12:38,864 --> 00:12:43,052
only to be done in by a jealous
Turk who hired assassins
to cut out his heart

166
00:12:43,151 --> 00:12:45,322
- He was only 30
- Black sheep?

167
00:12:45,422 --> 00:12:48,869
- One of three
- Well, I take it
you include yourself,

168
00:12:48,972 --> 00:12:50,794
but who's the third?

169
00:12:50,892 --> 00:12:53,760
My kid sister Marylee

170
00:12:53,866 --> 00:12:57,161
She's got enough devil in her
to put Uncle Joe and me
in the shade

171
00:12:57,257 --> 00:12:59,558
What's the matter?
Your ears burning?

172
00:12:59,657 --> 00:13:01,696
Just came to tell you
we're off the Carolina coast

173
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:04,383
- North Carolina?
- Uh-huh Are we turning back?

174
00:13:04,486 --> 00:13:06,590
Can't Automatic pilot's
set for Miami

175
00:13:06,693 --> 00:13:10,237
- And then what?
- I feel like a swim
How does Miami Beach sound?

176
00:13:10,340 --> 00:13:12,673
Better ask your guest

177
00:13:14,114 --> 00:13:16,928
Just say the word, and
I'll make a 180-degree turn

178
00:13:18,881 --> 00:13:20,767
Reluctantly?

179
00:13:20,864 --> 00:13:24,540
Uh-huh Something
is happening to me

180
00:13:24,639 --> 00:13:28,914
I find myself talking to you like
I never talked to anyone before...

181
00:13:29,021 --> 00:13:30,962
not even Mitch

182
00:13:31,069 --> 00:13:35,923
Please, Lucy I think we're past
the point of no return

183
00:13:41,881 --> 00:13:45,011
[Woman On PA]
Flight 498

184
00:13:45,112 --> 00:13:48,689
now arriving from Havana
at Cubana concourse

185
00:13:51,253 --> 00:13:54,448
Kyle's probably arranging
to buy you the hotel,

186
00:13:54,548 --> 00:13:56,751
a stretch of the beach
and a slice of the Gulf strip

187
00:13:58,131 --> 00:14:02,155
Why are you so sarcastic?
Do you resent our being here,

188
00:14:02,257 --> 00:14:06,030
or are you just disappointed that
I didn't ask Kyle to turn back?

189
00:14:07,919 --> 00:14:10,765
The first surprise
came at Teterborough

190
00:14:10,862 --> 00:14:12,933
I underestimated Kyle's charm

191
00:14:14,476 --> 00:14:17,671
Perhaps you've always
underestimated Kyle

192
00:14:17,771 --> 00:14:19,941
Or maybe you're
overestimating me

193
00:14:20,042 --> 00:14:23,521
- Could be
- Nothing like this has ever
happened to me before

194
00:14:23,624 --> 00:14:26,406
It's an adventure
It's exciting

195
00:14:27,783 --> 00:14:29,986
Are you looking for laughs?

196
00:14:30,086 --> 00:14:31,908
Or are you soul searching?

197
00:14:32,005 --> 00:14:33,827
The latter, I guess

198
00:14:36,036 --> 00:14:38,424
I think I'm beginning
to know Kyle

199
00:14:38,531 --> 00:14:40,919
and to like him

200
00:14:41,027 --> 00:14:43,360
Well, in that case, I'm glad

201
00:14:45,409 --> 00:14:47,230
I really am

202
00:14:50,367 --> 00:14:52,155
Tell me something

203
00:14:52,254 --> 00:14:55,253
This hooky-playing...
when does it end?

204
00:14:57,148 --> 00:14:58,970
I don't know

205
00:15:00,027 --> 00:15:02,230
For me,
it never seems to end

206
00:15:03,578 --> 00:15:05,552
Okay, kids
Let's beat it to Miami Beach

207
00:15:05,658 --> 00:15:08,918
Found us a boarding house with
built-in black-eyed peas and grits

208
00:15:19,189 --> 00:15:21,010
This way, please

209
00:15:24,466 --> 00:15:28,393
I'm certain, Mr. Hadley,
you'll find everything
to your satisfaction

210
00:15:28,497 --> 00:15:30,351
- Everything?
- Yes, sir

211
00:15:30,448 --> 00:15:32,269
Nice little boarding house
you have here

212
00:15:32,367 --> 00:15:35,464
- [Door Opens]
- This is Miss Moore's suite

213
00:15:35,566 --> 00:15:38,020
- And we're right across the hall?
- Yes, sir

214
00:16:00,037 --> 00:16:02,589
How do you like it?

215
00:16:02,692 --> 00:16:04,514
What's not to like, huh?

216
00:16:04,612 --> 00:16:06,913
Come on
I'll show you around

217
00:16:24,829 --> 00:16:26,650
Anything missing?

218
00:16:28,603 --> 00:16:30,425
Open the closet

219
00:16:42,805 --> 00:16:44,627
Look over here

220
00:16:56,911 --> 00:16:59,366
Great invention,
the telephone, hmm?

221
00:16:59,471 --> 00:17:01,293
See you in an hour, okay?

222
00:17:07,020 --> 00:17:08,841
[Door Closes]

223
00:17:31,492 --> 00:17:33,793
Sure floored her, didn't it?

224
00:17:33,890 --> 00:17:37,272
- Me too
- Sounds like a crack

225
00:17:37,377 --> 00:17:40,027
No, just a dent in my armor

226
00:17:40,129 --> 00:17:43,029
- What does that mean?
- Nothing much

227
00:17:45,278 --> 00:17:47,164
Except I had Lucy
figured wrong

228
00:17:47,260 --> 00:17:49,910
What did you expect?

229
00:17:50,012 --> 00:17:52,564
I figured she'd be different
than all the rest

230
00:17:52,666 --> 00:17:55,186
- She is
- No, she's not

231
00:17:59,448 --> 00:18:01,749
If she were, she'd have spit
right in your eye

232
00:18:03,351 --> 00:18:05,173
[Laughing]

233
00:18:09,332 --> 00:18:11,154
Lucy?

234
00:18:17,906 --> 00:18:19,760
Lucy, you decent?

235
00:18:24,143 --> 00:18:26,215
Lucy, are you dec...

236
00:18:37,131 --> 00:18:38,952
Guess she was

237
00:18:53,700 --> 00:18:55,804
- Yes, Mr. Hadley?
- Did you see Miss Moore leave?

238
00:18:55,907 --> 00:18:59,899
Yes, sir, I did...
about, uh, 30 minutes ago

239
00:19:01,346 --> 00:19:03,167
Yes, sir

240
00:19:03,265 --> 00:19:06,613
- Remember the girl who arrived
with me an hour ago?
- Yes, she left alone

241
00:19:06,719 --> 00:19:09,206
Took a cab to the airport

242
00:19:09,310 --> 00:19:11,611
The airport
Please step on it

243
00:19:15,068 --> 00:19:16,595
[Woman On PA]
Last call

244
00:19:16,700 --> 00:19:19,568
National Airlines,
flight 46 to New York,

245
00:19:19,675 --> 00:19:21,529
gate number five

246
00:19:21,626 --> 00:19:24,014
- All aboard
- Hello, Lucy

247
00:19:24,121 --> 00:19:26,324
Hello

248
00:19:26,424 --> 00:19:28,246
Please let me talk to you

249
00:19:28,343 --> 00:19:30,579
I left, didn't I?
Didn't that say enough?

250
00:19:30,679 --> 00:19:33,427
Yes, more than you know

251
00:19:33,525 --> 00:19:36,972
Please give me an hour...
just till the next plane leaves

252
00:19:38,996 --> 00:19:41,100
[Sighs]
All right

253
00:19:41,202 --> 00:19:43,406
[Woman On PA]
Pan American World Airways Clipper,

254
00:19:43,506 --> 00:19:45,480
flight 701

255
00:19:45,586 --> 00:19:48,584
for Buenos Aires
and intermediate cities

256
00:19:48,688 --> 00:19:51,273
now boarding
at Pan American concourse

257
00:19:58,861 --> 00:20:01,542
- Cream?
- Never use it

258
00:20:01,643 --> 00:20:03,497
Shows how little I know you

259
00:20:05,417 --> 00:20:07,489
Why'd you run out?

260
00:20:07,592 --> 00:20:10,690
I took a sudden dislike
to the suite

261
00:20:10,792 --> 00:20:13,212
Did I overdo it?

262
00:20:13,319 --> 00:20:16,700
Oh, it was beautiful
at first glance

263
00:20:16,806 --> 00:20:20,252
Then I thought how ugly
it would be in the morning

264
00:20:21,604 --> 00:20:24,799
You mean, the idea of
having fun?

265
00:20:24,898 --> 00:20:27,352
Wasn't that your intention?

266
00:20:27,458 --> 00:20:29,279
Guilty as charged

267
00:20:30,816 --> 00:20:33,117
I was tempted

268
00:20:33,216 --> 00:20:35,124
Was it easy to overcome?

269
00:20:35,231 --> 00:20:37,466
Yes You made it easy

270
00:20:37,566 --> 00:20:39,573
How, by throwing
my money at you?

271
00:20:39,677 --> 00:20:42,294
- No No, it wasn't that
- What, then?

272
00:20:42,396 --> 00:20:45,362
It was the ride

273
00:20:45,467 --> 00:20:48,051
"Up in the blue,"
as you call it

274
00:20:48,154 --> 00:20:50,575
Talked too much,
didn't I?

275
00:20:50,681 --> 00:20:53,364
No It was good talk

276
00:20:54,488 --> 00:20:57,520
Only something happened
to me...

277
00:20:57,622 --> 00:21:01,036
something unexpected
as the things you told me

278
00:21:01,141 --> 00:21:04,588
I tried to tell myself
it was, I don't know,

279
00:21:04,692 --> 00:21:07,408
sympathy, compassion

280
00:21:07,507 --> 00:21:09,329
But it was more

281
00:21:13,616 --> 00:21:16,615
Let's
let's get out of here

282
00:21:18,958 --> 00:21:20,779
Cigarette?

283
00:21:25,867 --> 00:21:28,354
We'll put you on the next plane
to New York

284
00:21:28,459 --> 00:21:30,280
Thank you

285
00:21:31,465 --> 00:21:33,287
I'm sorry, Lucy...

286
00:21:33,384 --> 00:21:37,376
sorrier than I've even been
in my whole sorry life

287
00:21:38,886 --> 00:21:41,122
I hope you believe me

288
00:21:41,222 --> 00:21:44,220
- Is it important that I do?
- Very,

289
00:21:44,325 --> 00:21:46,332
because I

290
00:21:46,436 --> 00:21:49,250
I want to start
all over again with you

291
00:21:50,627 --> 00:21:53,179
How?

292
00:21:53,281 --> 00:21:55,103
Suppose...

293
00:21:56,193 --> 00:21:58,875
Just suppose I came
to New York again

294
00:21:58,976 --> 00:22:02,553
Not to play,
but to work, to behave like...

295
00:22:02,654 --> 00:22:04,988
like Tom, Dick and Harry

296
00:22:05,086 --> 00:22:07,157
l-I'd ask you for dates,

297
00:22:07,261 --> 00:22:10,107
take you to lunches,
to the movies

298
00:22:10,203 --> 00:22:13,617
I'd be happy
with a good night kiss

299
00:22:15,257 --> 00:22:19,479
[Sighs]
I'd think seriously about all
the things I used to laugh at,

300
00:22:19,576 --> 00:22:23,349
like having a wife
and a home

301
00:22:24,405 --> 00:22:26,227
and kids

302
00:22:27,956 --> 00:22:32,559
Right now there's one thing
you don't have to suppose

303
00:22:34,162 --> 00:22:35,983
I'm in love with you

304
00:22:37,265 --> 00:22:41,290
So much so that
I want to marry you

305
00:23:02,440 --> 00:23:04,511
- Mitch Wayne?
- Yeah

306
00:23:04,615 --> 00:23:06,981
Jack Williams, Miami Press

307
00:23:07,078 --> 00:23:09,979
- Uh, care to say a few words
about the wedding?
- What wedding?

308
00:23:10,085 --> 00:23:14,524
We know that judge Ross issued
a marriage license this morning
to Kyle Hadley

309
00:23:14,628 --> 00:23:16,536
and, uh, Lucy Moore

310
00:23:16,643 --> 00:23:18,781
- So what?
- Who is Lucy Moore?

311
00:23:18,882 --> 00:23:20,704
- That's a good question
- You don't know her?

312
00:23:20,802 --> 00:23:23,451
- Not very well
- What is she?
A showgirl, model, what?

313
00:23:23,552 --> 00:23:25,973
Just a girl... a lady

314
00:23:27,487 --> 00:23:30,552
- A beautiful lady
- I got news for you, Mr. Wayne

315
00:23:30,653 --> 00:23:32,475
Your torch is burnin'

316
00:23:35,163 --> 00:23:38,009
- Wedding took place
two hours ago
- Yeah? Where?

317
00:23:39,353 --> 00:23:42,352
- Right under my nose
St Mark's Church
- Oh

318
00:23:42,457 --> 00:23:44,365
St Mark's Church

319
00:23:44,472 --> 00:23:48,082
Uh, Mr. Wayne
Hey, now wait up, Mr. Wayne

320
00:25:22,420 --> 00:25:24,721
- Pull up a chair
- Thank you, sir

321
00:25:27,858 --> 00:25:30,671
- How does it look to you?
- Promising

322
00:25:30,768 --> 00:25:32,590
How much
would you gamble on it?

323
00:25:32,688 --> 00:25:35,054
I think we ought to go
15,000 feet

324
00:25:36,623 --> 00:25:39,437
What do you hear from Kyle?

325
00:25:39,534 --> 00:25:42,794
The gossip columns say
they're in Acapulco

326
00:25:42,892 --> 00:25:45,924
When do you think I'm going to
get a chance to kiss the bride?

327
00:25:46,027 --> 00:25:48,709
- Six months from now? A year?
- [Chuckles]

328
00:25:48,810 --> 00:25:52,550
- It's only been five weeks
- Is that all?

329
00:25:54,119 --> 00:25:56,093
It's about time you got hitched,
isn't it?

330
00:25:58,150 --> 00:26:01,727
No, l... I have trouble enough
finding oil

331
00:26:01,828 --> 00:26:03,650
[Chuckles]

332
00:26:05,092 --> 00:26:07,611
I sure wish you felt different
about Marylee

333
00:26:10,721 --> 00:26:14,015
We grew up together,
like brother and sister

334
00:26:14,112 --> 00:26:16,445
I just can't see it
any other way

335
00:26:16,543 --> 00:26:18,365
Yeah

336
00:26:18,462 --> 00:26:21,047
It's a shame, though,
in a way

337
00:26:21,150 --> 00:26:23,418
It's a real shame

338
00:26:23,517 --> 00:26:26,483
- All right 5,000 feet No more
- Okay

339
00:26:28,987 --> 00:26:30,809
- Hi
- Hi!

340
00:26:30,906 --> 00:26:34,353
Mitch Mr. Hadley,
meet Mrs. Hadley

341
00:26:34,456 --> 00:26:36,823
Welcome to Hadley...

342
00:26:36,920 --> 00:26:39,341
the town and the family

343
00:26:39,447 --> 00:26:41,519
Thank you

344
00:26:41,623 --> 00:26:44,883
Well, son, l...
I just couldn't be happier

345
00:26:44,981 --> 00:26:46,803
- Did all right, didn't I?
- You sure did

346
00:26:46,900 --> 00:26:50,347
Now you vamoose for a few
minutes I want to talk
to my daughter-in-law alone

347
00:26:50,451 --> 00:26:52,589
Sure, Dad
I'll be in Mitch's office

348
00:26:55,506 --> 00:26:57,992
- Would you like a soft drink?
- No, thanks

349
00:26:58,096 --> 00:27:00,428
Just had one
in the drugstore

350
00:27:00,526 --> 00:27:03,908
- Have you been out
to the house?
- Yes, it's beautiful!

351
00:27:04,013 --> 00:27:05,900
And it's home

352
00:27:05,997 --> 00:27:08,417
- Did you meet Marylee?
- No, she was out

353
00:27:08,524 --> 00:27:12,832
Oh, that's too bad
l-I know she's gonna like you
just as much as I do

354
00:27:12,939 --> 00:27:15,752
I was afraid you might
be wary of me...

355
00:27:15,849 --> 00:27:18,598
that, perhaps, you'd regard me
as a gold digger

356
00:27:18,696 --> 00:27:21,151
[Laughs] Now, look
I'm gonna be honest with you

357
00:27:21,255 --> 00:27:24,254
That's just what I figured,
until I talked to Mitch

358
00:27:25,606 --> 00:27:28,452
Mitch? Interesting

359
00:27:28,548 --> 00:27:30,370
Yeah I wasn't easy
to convince,

360
00:27:30,467 --> 00:27:32,987
but Mitch sold me

361
00:27:33,091 --> 00:27:36,254
In other words,
you trust Mitch's judgment
more than Kyle's

362
00:27:36,354 --> 00:27:39,768
Well, I wouldn't put it
that way

363
00:27:41,504 --> 00:27:44,798
- May I ask you a favor?
- Anything at all

364
00:27:44,895 --> 00:27:49,149
Please give Kyle a chance
You may have to change
your opinion of him

365
00:27:49,245 --> 00:27:51,514
How much liquor
has he been puttin' away?

366
00:27:51,612 --> 00:27:54,426
I haven't seen him drunk yet

367
00:27:56,219 --> 00:27:58,040
Does he still...

368
00:27:58,905 --> 00:28:00,727
Well,

369
00:28:02,008 --> 00:28:04,375
I better not ask about that

370
00:28:05,687 --> 00:28:08,555
You mean, about the pistol
he keeps under his pillow

371
00:28:11,700 --> 00:28:15,179
- You know
- Yes

372
00:28:15,283 --> 00:28:18,630
I know all about his anxieties
and fears

373
00:28:19,762 --> 00:28:21,965
You can forget
about the pistol

374
00:28:22,064 --> 00:28:24,998
Kyle threw it in the ocean

375
00:28:25,264 --> 00:28:28,558
- I tell you,
I'm still up on cloud seven
- And sober too

376
00:28:28,654 --> 00:28:32,427
Yep, even in Mexico
Remember how I used to go
on those Tequila jags?

377
00:28:32,525 --> 00:28:35,491
- How could I forget?
- [Intercom Buzzes]

378
00:28:37,707 --> 00:28:40,804
- Yeah?
- A Mr. Willis calling
He says it's urgent

379
00:28:40,906 --> 00:28:42,880
Okay, put him on
Dan Willis

380
00:28:42,985 --> 00:28:45,406
- Mitch
- What is it, Dan?

381
00:28:47,719 --> 00:28:50,271
The Hadley gal's here
with Roy Carter

382
00:28:50,374 --> 00:28:52,315
Thanks, Dan
I'll be right over

383
00:28:52,422 --> 00:28:54,722
- You got a gun here?
- Stay here I'll handle it

384
00:28:54,820 --> 00:28:58,397
Dan said the Hadley gal
I'm the Hadley boy, remember?

385
00:29:00,611 --> 00:29:04,384
[Laughing]
That's a hot one, ain't it?

386
00:29:04,481 --> 00:29:07,000
Not very
I've heard better

387
00:29:08,288 --> 00:29:10,742
What's the matter, honey?
Are you insulted?

388
00:29:10,847 --> 00:29:12,668
Not yet

389
00:29:14,429 --> 00:29:16,251
Just bored

390
00:29:17,404 --> 00:29:19,346
The afternoon's wasting away

391
00:29:22,586 --> 00:29:24,887
I'll be right back

392
00:29:30,391 --> 00:29:32,626
How's the chances
of some privacy?

393
00:29:32,726 --> 00:29:36,467
Are you crazy, Roy?
If old man Hadley
ever found out,

394
00:29:36,565 --> 00:29:39,913
he'd have you sent so far away,
it'd take ten years
for a telegram to reach you

395
00:29:40,019 --> 00:29:43,498
- Give me the key
- Forget it You're stepping
out of your class

396
00:29:43,603 --> 00:29:46,863
You wouldn't like to have
this joint of yours catch fire
some night, would you?

397
00:29:51,503 --> 00:29:53,924
Give me a couple of minutes
to clean up

398
00:29:57,357 --> 00:29:59,179
Don't overdo it

399
00:30:18,213 --> 00:30:20,035
[Car Approaching]

400
00:30:33,535 --> 00:30:35,357
(music)(music) [Big Band]

401
00:30:52,216 --> 00:30:54,223
If I ever catch you
with my sister again, I'll...

402
00:30:54,328 --> 00:30:58,799
- Where do you want her
to play, in a sandbox?
- Honeymoon over?

403
00:30:58,902 --> 00:31:02,000
Are you forgetting where you are
and who you're with?

404
00:31:02,101 --> 00:31:05,067
Oh, be polite
Answer the lady

405
00:31:05,172 --> 00:31:06,994
Tell us all about...

406
00:31:27,564 --> 00:31:29,123
[Music Stops]

407
00:31:37,832 --> 00:31:40,612
Marylee, come on
We're getting out of here

408
00:31:44,069 --> 00:31:46,010
- Wait outside, Marylee
- [Gasps]

409
00:31:46,116 --> 00:31:49,890
- Step aside, Wayne,
before I cut you
- I would like to see that

410
00:31:51,970 --> 00:31:54,555
Hold it, Roy

411
00:31:54,657 --> 00:31:57,558
You bigmouth beer slinger
You phoned Wayne, didn't you?

412
00:31:57,664 --> 00:32:00,281
This gun's got a hair trigger

413
00:32:01,407 --> 00:32:03,228
Okay

414
00:32:05,022 --> 00:32:06,843
So I'm persuaded

415
00:32:15,514 --> 00:32:18,382
- Some other time, huh?
- You've had it

416
00:32:42,160 --> 00:32:45,290
- You take Kyle
and get out of here
- Thank you, Sir Galahad

417
00:32:45,391 --> 00:32:48,073
You do care about me,
don't you?

418
00:32:50,348 --> 00:32:52,736
- Let me have the gun, Dan
- Forget it

419
00:32:55,658 --> 00:32:57,480
Forget it

420
00:33:04,935 --> 00:33:06,756
I'll kill him

421
00:33:06,854 --> 00:33:09,308
A whiskey bottle's
about all you'd ever kill

422
00:33:20,353 --> 00:33:22,175
Sorry, Dan

423
00:33:25,472 --> 00:33:27,293
[Engine Idling]

424
00:33:55,221 --> 00:34:00,074
Mitch, let's go down to the river,
to our old haunt

425
00:34:02,098 --> 00:34:04,552
We used to be happy there

426
00:34:04,657 --> 00:34:08,878
Our own private world...
mine and yours

427
00:34:08,975 --> 00:34:10,796
and Kyle's

428
00:34:12,078 --> 00:34:13,965
Then you grew up and left me...

429
00:34:14,062 --> 00:34:16,101
you and Kyle...

430
00:34:16,204 --> 00:34:18,026
the rover boys

431
00:34:20,587 --> 00:34:22,888
I guess that's why
I hate him so...

432
00:34:25,226 --> 00:34:27,810
for taking you away

433
00:34:27,912 --> 00:34:29,733
from me

434
00:34:33,511 --> 00:34:36,063
I love you, Mitch

435
00:34:36,165 --> 00:34:38,019
I'm desperate for you

436
00:34:40,324 --> 00:34:43,672
So desperate, I run
to the likes of Roy Carter

437
00:34:45,570 --> 00:34:47,838
All right, blame me

438
00:34:49,665 --> 00:34:54,136
I'm not talking about blame
About love

439
00:34:57,118 --> 00:34:58,939
Do you love me, Mitch?

440
00:34:59,037 --> 00:35:00,858
Like a brother

441
00:35:02,428 --> 00:35:04,532
I don't want you
as a brother

442
00:35:04,635 --> 00:35:06,968
Can't be any other way,
Marylee

443
00:35:09,049 --> 00:35:14,132
Don't... Please don't waste your life
waiting for me

444
00:35:19,892 --> 00:35:22,477
I'll wait,

445
00:35:22,580 --> 00:35:25,099
and I'll have you,

446
00:35:25,203 --> 00:35:27,024
marriage

447
00:35:28,562 --> 00:35:30,383
or no marriage

448
00:35:38,094 --> 00:35:42,403
I'm Marylee
Welcome to Hadley, Sister-In-Law

449
00:35:42,509 --> 00:35:44,712
Thank you
Nice of you to come in and greet me

450
00:35:44,812 --> 00:35:47,113
Oh, please
I'm allergic to politeness

451
00:35:47,210 --> 00:35:51,202
By the way, your darling
husband should be taught
to mind his own business

452
00:35:51,305 --> 00:35:53,639
Should I apologize for him?

453
00:35:53,736 --> 00:35:57,957
[Chuckles]
You should have seen him...
on the wrong end of every punch

454
00:35:58,055 --> 00:36:00,062
And on the wrong end of town

455
00:36:01,509 --> 00:36:05,120
It isn't 21, but
it can be exciting

456
00:36:05,221 --> 00:36:07,521
What do you think of Mitch?

457
00:36:07,619 --> 00:36:10,040
You changed the subject

458
00:36:10,146 --> 00:36:13,276
Oh, there's a man for you...
or for me, rather

459
00:36:13,377 --> 00:36:16,278
Kyle starts something,
Mitch finishes it for him

460
00:36:16,385 --> 00:36:18,685
Kyle falls on his face,
Mitch picks him up

461
00:36:18,782 --> 00:36:21,116
Kyle steals,
Mitch takes the blame

462
00:36:21,213 --> 00:36:24,922
And there you have
the secret story of Kyle Hadley

463
00:36:25,020 --> 00:36:27,638
and his electric personality

464
00:36:27,739 --> 00:36:30,455
I've heard it
from Kyle himself

465
00:36:30,554 --> 00:36:34,262
Anyway, about your marriage,

466
00:36:34,361 --> 00:36:37,262
you have my condolences

467
00:36:37,368 --> 00:36:41,108
Pardon me if, uh, I seem to be
brushing you out of my hair

468
00:36:46,901 --> 00:36:50,794
Darling, I'll send you some
of my towels I believe you're
still wet behind the ears

469
00:36:52,563 --> 00:36:54,384
[Door Slams]

470
00:36:59,696 --> 00:37:01,102
[Dogs Panting]

471
00:37:01,615 --> 00:37:04,483
What was the matter
with you today, son?

472
00:37:04,590 --> 00:37:07,142
You were supposed to be
huntin', not broodin'

473
00:37:07,245 --> 00:37:09,633
- I'm sorry, Dad
- [Dogs Whimpering]

474
00:37:09,740 --> 00:37:11,561
[Dog Barking]

475
00:37:16,106 --> 00:37:17,927
Sit Sit!

476
00:37:19,081 --> 00:37:22,015
Anything we can talk about?

477
00:37:22,120 --> 00:37:26,046
- Did you ever hear of Iran?
- Africa? Asia? Asia, I guess

478
00:37:26,151 --> 00:37:29,247
- What about it?
- I'm thinking of going there

479
00:37:29,348 --> 00:37:31,616
- For Hadley?
- No

480
00:37:31,715 --> 00:37:33,656
Trans American Oil

481
00:37:33,763 --> 00:37:37,853
- Got a bellyful of the Hadleys?
- I guess so

482
00:37:37,953 --> 00:37:39,807
I sometimes wonder
if I did right by you...

483
00:37:39,904 --> 00:37:41,846
puttin' you with jasper
and his kids

484
00:37:41,952 --> 00:37:45,944
Meant it all for the best...
wanted you to have the chance
I had and didn't take

485
00:37:46,047 --> 00:37:49,974
I better level with you, Dad,
about why I'm leavin'

486
00:37:51,356 --> 00:37:54,421
I'm in love with a woman
that happens to be Kyle's wife

487
00:37:56,027 --> 00:37:58,447
- Is she in love with you?
- No

488
00:37:58,554 --> 00:38:00,375
Strictly one-sided

489
00:38:22,929 --> 00:38:25,579
[Young Kyle's Voice]
Bet you can't throw that far, Mitch

490
00:38:25,680 --> 00:38:28,297
[Young Marylee's Voice]
Mitch can do everything
better than you, Kyle

491
00:38:28,399 --> 00:38:31,562
- [Kyle]
Shut up, Marylee
- Throw it, Mitch

492
00:38:31,662 --> 00:38:33,865
- [Water Splashes]
- You did it, Mitch!

493
00:38:35,373 --> 00:38:37,674
[Kyle]
Last one across is a rotten egg

494
00:38:37,772 --> 00:38:40,072
[Water Splashing]

495
00:38:47,527 --> 00:38:49,348
[Kids Panting]

496
00:38:49,446 --> 00:38:52,293
[Young Mitch]
Hey, what's that purple stuff
on your lips?

497
00:38:52,389 --> 00:38:56,414
Mulberry juice
Looks like lipstick, doesn't it?

498
00:38:56,516 --> 00:38:59,035
Yeah, sure does

499
00:38:59,139 --> 00:39:01,723
Mitch, am I beautiful?

500
00:39:01,826 --> 00:39:04,542
- Uh-huh
- Do you love me?

501
00:39:04,642 --> 00:39:07,096
Sure You're my girl

502
00:39:07,200 --> 00:39:11,094
When we grow up,
you'll marry me, won't you, Mitch?

503
00:39:11,199 --> 00:39:13,500
I love you so much

504
00:39:21,243 --> 00:39:23,065
[Sobbing]

505
00:39:27,769 --> 00:39:29,591
(music)(music) [Big Band]

506
00:39:40,404 --> 00:39:43,120
[Chattering, Laughing]

507
00:39:43,220 --> 00:39:46,153
It's gonna be a great football game
Could put us in the Cotton Bowl

508
00:39:46,259 --> 00:39:48,591
Putting me in Dallas
is what I like about it

509
00:39:48,688 --> 00:39:51,175
- I never know who's got the ball
- [Laughs]

510
00:40:06,665 --> 00:40:08,487
(music)(music) [Plucking Ukulele]

511
00:40:13,736 --> 00:40:15,557
(music)(music) [Strums]

512
00:40:19,365 --> 00:40:22,266
A drink
for your thoughts

513
00:40:22,373 --> 00:40:25,536
Congratulate me
I've just been voted
the life of the party

514
00:40:25,635 --> 00:40:27,457
[Chuckles]

515
00:40:29,857 --> 00:40:33,239
Your old room

516
00:40:33,344 --> 00:40:36,987
- All those wonderful afternoons
we used to spend here
- (music)(music) [Playing Softly]

517
00:40:38,494 --> 00:40:41,308
And it rained

518
00:40:41,406 --> 00:40:45,747
Well, it was too cold for us
to go down to the river haunt

519
00:40:47,516 --> 00:40:50,831
Yes, those wonderful
lost afternoons

520
00:41:03,477 --> 00:41:06,574
That's a nice dress...
real flattering

521
00:41:06,675 --> 00:41:09,838
I've changed since we
last swam in the raw, haven't I?

522
00:41:12,626 --> 00:41:14,665
A long, long time ago

523
00:41:14,768 --> 00:41:16,840
I was an idiot boy then

524
00:41:16,944 --> 00:41:18,765
Yes, you were

525
00:41:21,166 --> 00:41:24,809
The other idiot boy's downstairs
having himself a big party

526
00:41:26,572 --> 00:41:28,426
It's a happy occasion, isn't it?

527
00:41:29,483 --> 00:41:31,588
Unbelievable

528
00:41:31,690 --> 00:41:34,821
Married a whole year
and still sober

529
00:41:34,921 --> 00:41:36,743
and still faithful

530
00:41:36,841 --> 00:41:39,687
It can't last much longer

531
00:41:41,639 --> 00:41:43,460
Don't sell Lucy short

532
00:41:43,558 --> 00:41:47,070
[Scoffs] There's only so much
a woman can do, and no more

533
00:41:49,252 --> 00:41:52,960
I speak from
personal experience

534
00:41:53,059 --> 00:41:54,880
with you

535
00:41:55,938 --> 00:41:58,555
You know,
you're remarkable

536
00:41:58,657 --> 00:42:03,162
You've got your axe buried
in Kyle's head, and you're
grinding it at the same time

537
00:42:03,263 --> 00:42:07,484
- I can think of much better
things than making small talk
- Oh

538
00:42:10,396 --> 00:42:12,217
All right Let's dance

539
00:42:13,275 --> 00:42:15,445
[Sighs]
Still the idiot boy

540
00:42:24,662 --> 00:42:27,596
Oh, thank you, Dad!

541
00:42:30,228 --> 00:42:32,595
Oh, it's beautiful

542
00:42:32,691 --> 00:42:34,513
Thank you, Lucy

543
00:42:34,611 --> 00:42:37,260
What about the poor
struggling husband?
Don't I get anything?

544
00:42:37,362 --> 00:42:40,361
- Well, what more
do you want, son?
- Another big party

545
00:42:40,464 --> 00:42:42,951
Only next time,
we'll invite the stork

546
00:42:43,056 --> 00:42:44,877
[Nervous Chuckle]

547
00:43:34,237 --> 00:43:36,058
(music)[Waltz]

548
00:43:37,947 --> 00:43:41,077
- Beats prescription liquor,
doesn't it, Doc?
- It sure does

549
00:43:41,178 --> 00:43:43,316
Just a second, Doc, please

550
00:43:43,417 --> 00:43:46,580
- Do me a favor
- just name it

551
00:43:46,680 --> 00:43:48,719
Ask Lucy to pay you a visit

552
00:43:50,295 --> 00:43:54,385
- She's been visiting me regularly
- She has?

553
00:43:54,485 --> 00:43:58,346
Look, why don't we have
a powwow in my office
about 10:00 in the morning?

554
00:43:58,452 --> 00:44:00,687
It won't keep

555
00:44:00,787 --> 00:44:03,655
Tell me, is, is Lucy all right?

556
00:44:05,169 --> 00:44:09,478
Well, what I mean is
can she have children?

557
00:44:09,584 --> 00:44:12,550
- Tomorrow we'll sit down and...
- Now, Doc

558
00:44:12,655 --> 00:44:14,476
Please

559
00:44:15,918 --> 00:44:17,957
There's nothing wrong with Lucy

560
00:44:56,575 --> 00:44:59,508
Well, your wife's
a wonderful dancer

561
00:45:00,828 --> 00:45:03,216
Kyle, what's the matter?

562
00:45:03,324 --> 00:45:05,974
- Come on Dance with me
- Can't

563
00:45:06,074 --> 00:45:09,651
Somebody just stole my
magic dancing slippers

564
00:45:33,521 --> 00:45:35,342
Anyone for lunch?

565
00:45:37,264 --> 00:45:39,683
Don't tell me where
I'll find my way

566
00:45:39,790 --> 00:45:44,163
Glory be Maybe you finally
see the light in my eyes

567
00:45:44,268 --> 00:45:46,209
[Engine Starts]

568
00:46:03,301 --> 00:46:05,634
Oh, there's nothing
like a picnic,

569
00:46:05,732 --> 00:46:08,578
and I've brought everything
but rain and ants

570
00:46:08,675 --> 00:46:11,708
Oh, correction
Everything but rain
[Blows]

571
00:46:11,810 --> 00:46:14,144
Anything happen at the house
after I left the party?

572
00:46:14,241 --> 00:46:16,281
[Chuckles]
Didn't miss a thing,

573
00:46:16,384 --> 00:46:19,165
except the sight of me
sleeping in your old room

574
00:46:20,223 --> 00:46:22,294
Did Kyle have a spat
with Lucy?

575
00:46:23,902 --> 00:46:27,513
That's why you gave in
and came here with me...
to play 20 questions

576
00:46:27,612 --> 00:46:29,434
Well, did he or didn't he?

577
00:46:29,532 --> 00:46:33,491
I don't know
All I know is he bit
my head off this morning

578
00:46:33,595 --> 00:46:35,416
Why?
What'd you say to him?

579
00:46:35,514 --> 00:46:39,822
That he looked sick
All I said was, "I trust
it's nothing trivial"

580
00:46:39,928 --> 00:46:42,993
- Do you...
- Oh, please
No more questions

581
00:46:45,462 --> 00:46:47,827
Let's eat,

582
00:46:47,924 --> 00:46:50,542
drink and be merry

583
00:46:52,883 --> 00:46:55,021
We'll eat, drink and run

584
00:46:55,121 --> 00:46:58,251
If Lucy were here with you,
I bet you wouldn't say that

585
00:46:58,352 --> 00:47:01,133
I once washed your mouth out
with soap I can do it again

586
00:47:01,231 --> 00:47:03,053
[Chuckles]
I know you, Mitch

587
00:47:03,150 --> 00:47:05,538
No one will ever know you
as I know you

588
00:47:07,501 --> 00:47:09,322
[Chuckles]

589
00:47:09,420 --> 00:47:11,242
[Both Women]
Good morning, Doctor

590
00:47:17,258 --> 00:47:20,518
- What's the story?
- I believe we'll have to make
some further tests...

591
00:47:20,617 --> 00:47:23,136
What is it?
Yes or no?

592
00:47:23,240 --> 00:47:25,344
Kyle, it's not that simple

593
00:47:25,447 --> 00:47:27,999
No apologies Facts

594
00:47:28,101 --> 00:47:31,134
- What'll you have, Doctor?
- Oh, just a limeade, Sherry
No ice

595
00:47:31,236 --> 00:47:33,657
Yes, Doctor

596
00:47:33,763 --> 00:47:35,618
The tests we took show a...

597
00:47:35,715 --> 00:47:38,497
Well, let's call it a weakness

598
00:47:41,921 --> 00:47:44,059
Believe me,
you're not sterile

599
00:47:45,791 --> 00:47:48,725
And there is hope, real hope,
that, in time,

600
00:47:48,830 --> 00:47:51,131
we'll be able to correct
that weakness

601
00:48:16,563 --> 00:48:18,385
[Phone Ringing]

602
00:48:23,313 --> 00:48:25,767
- Hello?
- Marylee, it's Mitch

603
00:48:25,872 --> 00:48:28,970
Oh, yes Brother Mitch

604
00:48:29,071 --> 00:48:31,655
Kyle just phoned me
He wants us, you and me,

605
00:48:31,758 --> 00:48:34,124
to join him and Lucy
at the country club for dinner

606
00:48:34,221 --> 00:48:36,522
Look, I'll pick you up
at 6:00, okay?

607
00:48:36,620 --> 00:48:40,481
Don't bother, Mitch,
not unless you have
an exciting evening in mind

608
00:48:40,587 --> 00:48:43,782
And you know exactly what I mean
by an exciting evening

609
00:48:53,670 --> 00:48:55,491
[Grunts]

610
00:49:15,869 --> 00:49:19,381
- Good evenin' Fill her up?
- Yes

611
00:49:20,476 --> 00:49:23,257
You're Biff Miley, aren't you?

612
00:49:23,355 --> 00:49:26,321
Nice of you to recognize me
without my shoulder pads

613
00:49:26,426 --> 00:49:28,432
Your number's
in my program

614
00:49:28,537 --> 00:49:31,253
I recognized you too,
Miss Hadley

615
00:49:31,351 --> 00:49:34,350
You do?
What do we do now?

616
00:49:34,455 --> 00:49:36,974
Break into a chorus
of"Hail, Alma Mater"?

617
00:49:40,213 --> 00:49:42,067
I close up
in half an hour

618
00:49:43,795 --> 00:49:45,834
You mean, usually

619
00:49:45,938 --> 00:49:49,133
All right
Just keep the motor running

620
00:49:53,007 --> 00:49:55,789
- (music)[Jazz]
- [Chattering, Laughing]

621
00:50:00,621 --> 00:50:03,490
- Good evening, jack
Is Mr. Hadley here yet?
- Oh, yes, ma'am

622
00:50:03,596 --> 00:50:05,701
Hello, Lucy
What's up?

623
00:50:05,803 --> 00:50:07,810
I was hoping
you could tell me

624
00:50:07,914 --> 00:50:10,280
I haven't seen Kyle since
he left the house this morning

625
00:50:10,378 --> 00:50:13,377
He phoned me about an hour ago
and said we were having dinner
at the club

626
00:50:13,480 --> 00:50:15,302
Well, he phoned me too

627
00:50:17,191 --> 00:50:19,012
Kyle

628
00:50:24,931 --> 00:50:26,753
Howdy

629
00:50:28,130 --> 00:50:30,431
Good evening, Mrs. Hadley,
Mr. Wayne

630
00:50:30,530 --> 00:50:32,668
Good evening

631
00:50:32,768 --> 00:50:35,189
- Set 'em up, Ben
- Yes, sir

632
00:50:37,983 --> 00:50:40,949
- Where's little sister?
- Couldn't locate her

633
00:50:41,054 --> 00:50:44,369
She'll never, never be missed

634
00:50:44,476 --> 00:50:47,737
- Will she, honey?
- Will she what?

635
00:50:47,835 --> 00:50:52,689
Be missed
Haven't you learned to hate
Marylee as much as I do?

636
00:50:54,201 --> 00:50:56,023
A toast to...

637
00:50:59,543 --> 00:51:01,909
to beauty

638
00:51:02,006 --> 00:51:05,779
and the truth,
which is anything but beautiful

639
00:51:09,300 --> 00:51:12,048
Come on
Let's have some dinner

640
00:51:12,147 --> 00:51:15,691
Honey, this is an occasion

641
00:51:15,793 --> 00:51:20,232
We must proceed with,
with quiet dignity

642
00:51:20,335 --> 00:51:23,596
What, um...
what are we celebrating?

643
00:51:23,694 --> 00:51:26,214
The end of a drought...

644
00:51:26,317 --> 00:51:28,203
a yearlong drought

645
00:51:29,260 --> 00:51:31,081
We drank a toast to truth

646
00:51:31,179 --> 00:51:35,269
- So?
- You ought to let us in on what
you're really celebrating

647
00:51:35,369 --> 00:51:37,191
or mourning

648
00:51:37,289 --> 00:51:39,110
[Laughing]

649
00:51:39,208 --> 00:51:41,957
- Ben, quick The potions
- Yes, sir

650
00:51:43,399 --> 00:51:45,885
So you'd like to know
my secret

651
00:51:47,621 --> 00:51:51,198
The secret is

652
00:51:51,299 --> 00:51:56,000
not to pour the vermouth, just
to pretend you're pouring it
[Laughing]

653
00:52:00,928 --> 00:52:02,750
[Laughing Continues]

654
00:52:16,219 --> 00:52:18,519
Those lousy cops again

655
00:52:26,167 --> 00:52:28,981
I'm sorry, Ralph
I didn't mean to blow up like that,

656
00:52:29,046 --> 00:52:32,558
but I'm getting a little sick and tired
of your efficiency experts

657
00:52:32,661 --> 00:52:35,791
They ought to get off
their chairs and out in
the field for a change

658
00:52:38,418 --> 00:52:42,159
All right, Ralph
I'll see you in New York
Thursday morning Bye

659
00:53:04,840 --> 00:53:07,621
I thought I'd seen
the last of this

660
00:53:07,719 --> 00:53:11,263
I wish I could,
but I can't explain it

661
00:53:11,366 --> 00:53:14,528
- Where have you been?
- The country club

662
00:53:15,589 --> 00:53:18,686
- Did you have a spat?
- [Sighs] No

663
00:53:18,787 --> 00:53:21,372
Nothing as simple as that

664
00:53:21,474 --> 00:53:26,295
We let him drink,
hoping he'd talk and tell us
what was on his mind

665
00:53:28,192 --> 00:53:30,493
But we learned nothing,

666
00:53:30,591 --> 00:53:34,234
except that
he's terribly tormented

667
00:53:34,333 --> 00:53:36,569
What are you
going to do now?

668
00:53:38,140 --> 00:53:41,522
Go to him and try to help him

669
00:53:53,590 --> 00:53:58,443
[Moaning]
Kid Kid stuff, Mitch

670
00:54:00,147 --> 00:54:05,263
I want to buy a new car,
the first flashy car

671
00:54:05,361 --> 00:54:08,524
To hell with college
I wanna have fun

672
00:54:08,625 --> 00:54:11,373
with some girls

673
00:54:11,471 --> 00:54:13,358
Nice over in Dallas

674
00:54:13,455 --> 00:54:15,276
To hell with college

675
00:54:18,061 --> 00:54:20,711
Wanna make some money, Mitch?

676
00:54:20,812 --> 00:54:25,829
Over at the bottling plant
Old man Daley's place

677
00:54:25,930 --> 00:54:30,184
[Chuckles]
No, I haven't got any bottles
Old man Daley has

678
00:54:31,464 --> 00:54:34,845
[Moaning Continues]

679
00:54:34,951 --> 00:54:38,397
Don't touch me
Touch me, I'll tell my father

680
00:54:38,502 --> 00:54:42,429
That's what I'll do
My father

681
00:54:42,532 --> 00:54:45,313
We weren't stealing,
were we, Mitch?

682
00:54:45,411 --> 00:54:48,825
We were just stacking
some bottles up for you

683
00:54:48,930 --> 00:54:51,580
That's all we were doing,
wasn't it, Mitch?

684
00:54:51,681 --> 00:54:54,429
Mitch? Mitch

685
00:54:54,528 --> 00:54:57,592
Wait for me
Wait for me!

686
00:54:57,694 --> 00:55:01,948
I remember
I stopped the surgeon just
before he went in to operate

687
00:55:02,044 --> 00:55:05,720
I said, " Doctor, I'll write
a check for a million dollars,

688
00:55:05,819 --> 00:55:08,851
but just don't let my wife die"

689
00:55:08,954 --> 00:55:10,775
But I failed

690
00:55:13,304 --> 00:55:15,126
[Mutters]

691
00:55:21,109 --> 00:55:22,996
I failed them all...

692
00:55:23,093 --> 00:55:24,947
my wife
and my brother Joe

693
00:55:26,003 --> 00:55:28,588
Both my children

694
00:55:28,690 --> 00:55:30,991
I think you're being
too hard on yourself

695
00:55:31,090 --> 00:55:32,912
[Car Approaching]

696
00:56:19,391 --> 00:56:22,041
Where did you first meet
my daughter?

697
00:56:22,143 --> 00:56:25,786
I never met her before, not till
she picked me up tonight

698
00:56:25,885 --> 00:56:28,884
- She picked you up?
- Sure

699
00:56:28,988 --> 00:56:32,761
- That's how she operates
- What do you mean, "operates"?

700
00:56:32,859 --> 00:56:35,313
I never heard of anybody
pickin' her up That's all

701
00:56:35,418 --> 00:56:37,239
It's always
the other way around

702
00:56:37,337 --> 00:56:39,638
How would you know?

703
00:56:39,737 --> 00:56:43,510
Why don't you just walk
up and down Main Street
and ask somebody?

704
00:56:43,607 --> 00:56:45,428
I'm asking you!

705
00:56:46,934 --> 00:56:49,202
Look, I don't like
to shoot my mouth off

706
00:56:49,301 --> 00:56:51,122
I also don't like
being on the carpet

707
00:56:51,220 --> 00:56:53,521
I didn't take her to the motel
She took me

708
00:56:53,619 --> 00:56:58,320
Your daughter's a tramp, mister
If that ain't plain enough,
I could put...

709
00:57:10,094 --> 00:57:13,224
- Get him out of here
- Should we hold him?

710
00:57:13,325 --> 00:57:15,266
No Let him go

711
00:57:17,833 --> 00:57:20,167
Keep it quiet, if you can

712
00:57:21,384 --> 00:57:23,936
Thanks
Thanks a lot

713
00:57:40,098 --> 00:57:42,269
[Engine Starts]

714
00:57:42,369 --> 00:57:44,191
[Car Departs]

715
00:57:59,163 --> 00:58:01,944
(music)(music) [jazz]

716
00:58:25,616 --> 00:58:28,397
(music)[Continues]

717
01:00:15,688 --> 01:00:18,021
- Kyle?
- Hmm?

718
01:00:18,119 --> 01:00:19,941
When is it going to end?

719
01:00:21,702 --> 01:00:23,840
You never know

720
01:00:23,941 --> 01:00:27,137
Things have a way
of happening so suddenly,

721
01:00:27,235 --> 01:00:29,057
unexpectedly

722
01:00:29,155 --> 01:00:31,642
- What's wrong?
- What isn't?

723
01:00:31,746 --> 01:00:34,167
Me and my darling sister...

724
01:00:35,233 --> 01:00:37,403
we pushed Dad
down the stairs

725
01:00:38,592 --> 01:00:41,112
You started drinking
before your father died

726
01:00:41,215 --> 01:00:44,149
Yeah,
I was 14 years old

727
01:00:46,172 --> 01:00:48,658
- Kyle
- Hmm?

728
01:00:50,043 --> 01:00:52,147
Do you love me?

729
01:00:52,250 --> 01:00:54,071
Love you?

730
01:00:55,320 --> 01:00:57,491
I don't even love myself

731
01:00:59,415 --> 01:01:03,276
Kyle, what is it?
Is it something I've said

732
01:01:03,382 --> 01:01:07,853
or something I've done
or should have done?

733
01:01:07,956 --> 01:01:10,737
I can't tell you

734
01:01:10,835 --> 01:01:13,223
I'm afraid

735
01:01:13,330 --> 01:01:16,974
It's like I was deep
in a mountain pass,

736
01:01:17,073 --> 01:01:20,236
snowcaps hanging
over my head

737
01:01:20,336 --> 01:01:22,407
If I make a sound,

738
01:01:22,511 --> 01:01:24,812
snow might all come
tumbling down

739
01:01:25,869 --> 01:01:29,959
Bury me alive

740
01:02:10,557 --> 01:02:12,531
- Good morning
- Good morning, Lucy

741
01:02:12,636 --> 01:02:15,635
- Would you like some coffee?
- Yes, thanks

742
01:02:29,910 --> 01:02:31,884
You look ill

743
