998
01:24:47,012 --> 01:24:50,622
- I didn't take anything from you
- Lousy white trash, say a prayer

999
01:24:50,723 --> 01:24:53,918
You know who you sound like?
Old man Daley

1000
01:24:54,018 --> 01:24:57,432
Remember old man Daley
and the bottles?

1001
01:24:57,536 --> 01:24:59,641
It was your idea
to steal them

1002
01:24:59,743 --> 01:25:02,328
I couldn't talk you out of it,
so I went along

1003
01:25:02,430 --> 01:25:05,277
But when he caught us, he didn't
blame you, he blamed me

1004
01:25:05,374 --> 01:25:07,860
And he grabbed me and he
kicked the tar out of me

1005
01:25:07,964 --> 01:25:10,745
I remember him saying,
"This is what Hadley gets

1006
01:25:10,843 --> 01:25:13,110
for letting his boy
play with trash like you"

1007
01:25:13,210 --> 01:25:15,664
He had you pegged right
You are trash!

1008
01:25:15,769 --> 01:25:19,280
I took the blame for stealing
those bottles, just like
I've always taken the blame,

1009
01:25:19,383 --> 01:25:21,205
but I'm not gonna take it
for this

1010
01:25:21,302 --> 01:25:25,076
Kyle, we've never lied
to each other

1011
01:25:25,174 --> 01:25:29,100
And I'm telling you now,
I never touched Lucy,

1012
01:25:29,204 --> 01:25:31,821
only because she's your wife

1013
01:25:31,923 --> 01:25:34,671
Get this straight

1014
01:25:34,770 --> 01:25:36,874
The child would have been yours

1015
01:25:38,384 --> 01:25:40,653
Not mine

1016
01:25:40,751 --> 01:25:42,573
Yours

1017
01:25:43,982 --> 01:25:46,370
- Lousy white trash!
- Kyle!

1018
01:25:46,478 --> 01:25:49,259
- [Gunshot]
- Kyle!

1019
01:25:53,323 --> 01:25:55,046
Mitch?

1020
01:25:55,146 --> 01:25:57,601
Yeah?

1021
01:25:57,706 --> 01:25:59,909
What are we doing here, Mitch?

1022
01:26:00,009 --> 01:26:02,179
What are we doing?

1023
01:26:03,975 --> 01:26:06,079
Let's go down to the river

1024
01:26:08,198 --> 01:26:10,172
where we belong

1025
01:26:25,023 --> 01:26:28,218
[Mitch]
Operator, rush an ambulance
to the Hadley estate

1026
01:26:32,732 --> 01:26:35,153
I'll be down at the river,

1027
01:26:35,259 --> 01:26:37,081
waiting

1028
01:26:38,138 --> 01:26:39,960
Waiting

1029
01:26:56,723 --> 01:26:58,545
I was just thinking

1030
01:27:03,633 --> 01:27:05,487
You know,

1031
01:27:05,585 --> 01:27:07,656
you threatened to kill Kyle

1032
01:27:07,760 --> 01:27:09,701
The servants heard you

1033
01:27:09,807 --> 01:27:11,628
Also Dr Cochrane

1034
01:27:11,726 --> 01:27:13,548
and Yours Truly

1035
01:27:15,692 --> 01:27:17,514
So what?

1036
01:27:19,435 --> 01:27:22,249
I could tell the police

1037
01:27:22,346 --> 01:27:24,964
that I saw you kill
my dear brother

1038
01:27:26,985 --> 01:27:28,806
You could

1039
01:27:33,029 --> 01:27:34,851
On the other hand,

1040
01:27:36,452 --> 01:27:38,273
a wife wouldn't

1041
01:27:38,371 --> 01:27:41,370
and couldn't testify
against her own husband

1042
01:27:46,304 --> 01:27:49,598
You know, for a beautiful girl,
you can look real ugly sometimes

1043
01:27:51,359 --> 01:27:53,627
Ask yourself this:

1044
01:27:53,726 --> 01:27:55,667
Would I ever be enough for you?

1045
01:27:57,501 --> 01:28:00,566
I can talk you right into
the state penitentiary

1046
01:28:02,459 --> 01:28:05,360
You're sick, Marylee

1047
01:28:05,466 --> 01:28:08,760
Your sickness won't be cured
by marrying me

1048
01:28:10,360 --> 01:28:12,879
Before it's too late,
you'd better face up to yourself

1049
01:28:15,798 --> 01:28:18,164
Look how far we've come
from the river

1050
01:28:42,860 --> 01:28:44,899
Raise your right hand, please

1051
01:28:45,002 --> 01:28:47,522
Do you swear the testimony
you're about to give in this inquest

1052
01:28:47,625 --> 01:28:49,861
is the truth, the whole truth
and nothing but the truth,
so help you God?

1053
01:28:49,961 --> 01:28:52,000
- I do
- [Judge]
Dr Cochrane,

1054
01:28:52,104 --> 01:28:54,438
would you tell this inquest
about the threat, please?

1055
01:28:55,975 --> 01:29:00,992
When I asked Mr. Wayne
where Kyle Hadley was,

1056
01:29:01,093 --> 01:29:04,638
he said, "I don't know,
but he'd better not
come back here tonight"

1057
01:29:04,739 --> 01:29:06,811
Thank you, Doctor
Next witness

1058
01:29:06,914 --> 01:29:10,459
My wife She said to me,
"There's gonna be a killin'

1059
01:29:10,561 --> 01:29:15,710
I heard talk Mr. Mitch said
he's gonna kill Mr. Kyle"

1060
01:29:15,807 --> 01:29:17,629
Thank you
Next witness

1061
01:29:17,727 --> 01:29:20,987
That's what I heard...

1062
01:29:21,086 --> 01:29:25,176
Mr. Mitch yellin'
and sayin' to Mr. Kyle,

1063
01:29:25,276 --> 01:29:27,098
"Get out of here!

1064
01:29:27,196 --> 01:29:29,944
Get out
be-before I kill you!"

1065
01:29:30,042 --> 01:29:33,619
- [Crying]
- Thank you Thank you
very much Next witness

1066
01:29:33,722 --> 01:29:37,168
Well, Kyle looked all beat up
I said, "What's with you?"

1067
01:29:37,272 --> 01:29:39,791
He said,
"Somebody tried to kill me"

1068
01:29:39,895 --> 01:29:43,406
I asked who, and he said,
"My best friend"

1069
01:29:43,510 --> 01:29:45,484
Did he mention a name?

1070
01:29:45,589 --> 01:29:47,727
No, he didn't have to

1071
01:29:47,828 --> 01:29:49,649
Why not?

1072
01:29:49,747 --> 01:29:53,639
Well, everybody knows
that Kyle's best friend
was Mitch Wayne

1073
01:29:53,745 --> 01:29:57,453
- Thank you, Mr. Willis
That'll be all Next witness
- [Murmuring]

1074
01:29:57,552 --> 01:30:02,155
Can you tell us if, at any time,
you heard Mitch Wayne threaten
to kill your husband?

1075
01:30:02,254 --> 01:30:04,228
Mitch Wayne did not kill
my husband

1076
01:30:04,334 --> 01:30:07,267
That wasn't my question

1077
01:30:07,372 --> 01:30:11,396
I asked you if, at any time,
you heard Mitch Wayne threaten
to kill your husband

1078
01:30:13,034 --> 01:30:15,848
- Yes, but...
- Thank you That will be all

1079
01:30:15,945 --> 01:30:18,050
Will Miss Hadley
step forward, please?

1080
01:30:18,152 --> 01:30:19,974
[Crowd Murmuring]

1081
01:30:24,518 --> 01:30:27,386
- [Man]
State your name, please
- Marylee Hadley

1082
01:30:27,493 --> 01:30:29,532
Do you swear the testimony
you're about to give

1083
01:30:29,637 --> 01:30:31,676
is the truth
and nothing but the truth?

1084
01:30:31,779 --> 01:30:33,601
- I do
- Be seated

1085
01:30:33,699 --> 01:30:38,585
You can refuse to answer
any question you may regard
as incriminating

1086
01:30:40,289 --> 01:30:43,484
What was your relation
to the deceased?

1087
01:30:43,583 --> 01:30:46,167
He was my brother

1088
01:30:46,270 --> 01:30:49,564
Exactly where were you at
the time Kyle Hadley was shot?

1089
01:30:55,739 --> 01:30:57,746
I repeat, Miss Hadley,

1090
01:30:57,850 --> 01:31:01,230
exactly where were you at
the time Kyle Hadley was shot?

1091
01:31:04,694 --> 01:31:07,214
You refuse to answer
the question?

1092
01:31:09,748 --> 01:31:12,595
Can you tell us anything
about the shooting?

1093
01:31:12,692 --> 01:31:16,432
Yes My brother,
he was killed

1094
01:31:18,129 --> 01:31:20,103
By whom, Miss Hadley?

1095
01:31:20,209 --> 01:31:22,313
By whom
was your brother killed?

1096
01:31:30,382 --> 01:31:34,504
- Mitch Wayne
- [Indistinct Chatter]

1097
01:31:34,604 --> 01:31:36,992
Stop those men!

1098
01:31:37,099 --> 01:31:40,513
No one will leave this chamber
till after this inquest is closed

1099
01:31:40,618 --> 01:31:42,526
[Chattering Continues]

1100
01:31:44,169 --> 01:31:46,110
Miss Hadley,

1101
01:31:46,215 --> 01:31:48,037
you named Mitch Wayne

1102
01:31:48,135 --> 01:31:50,468
Are you here and now
testifying

1103
01:31:50,566 --> 01:31:52,899
that Mitch Wayne shot
and killed Kyle Hadley?

1104
01:31:59,779 --> 01:32:03,073
Mitch Wayne was there

1105
01:32:04,801 --> 01:32:06,807
in the study
with my brother

1106
01:32:09,280 --> 01:32:11,383
Kyle had a gun in his hand

1107
01:32:11,486 --> 01:32:13,340
He was raving mad...

1108
01:32:14,493 --> 01:32:17,754
raving about things
that weren't so

1109
01:32:18,843 --> 01:32:21,144
Mitch tried
to talk to him,

1110
01:32:21,242 --> 01:32:23,608
to make him understand
how wrong he was,

1111
01:32:24,696 --> 01:32:26,736
to stop him
from using the gun

1112
01:32:28,824 --> 01:32:31,157
Afraid he might even use it
on himself

1113
01:32:31,255 --> 01:32:33,425
I made a grab for the gun

1114
01:32:33,526 --> 01:32:35,348
Kyle and I struggled

1115
01:32:37,556 --> 01:32:39,378
The gun went off

1116
01:32:41,043 --> 01:32:43,792
Miss Hadley,
five persons under oath

1117
01:32:43,890 --> 01:32:47,783
have testified that Mitch Wayne
threatened to kill Kyle Hadley

1118
01:32:56,973 --> 01:33:00,649
They don't know Mitch Wayne
as I know him

1119
01:33:02,027 --> 01:33:04,001
Whatever he may have said

1120
01:33:05,610 --> 01:33:07,682
means nothing

1121
01:33:08,873 --> 01:33:11,938
Except he was worried
about Kyle

1122
01:33:12,040 --> 01:33:14,788
as a brother for a brother

1123
01:33:14,887 --> 01:33:18,202
Why would Kyle Hadley
want to kill himself?

1124
01:33:18,310 --> 01:33:21,406
He was depressed

1125
01:33:22,819 --> 01:33:25,208
by Father's sudden death,

1126
01:33:27,393 --> 01:33:29,215
and he'd been drinking

1127
01:33:30,272 --> 01:33:31,733
Heavily?

1128
01:33:32,864 --> 01:33:34,935
[Sighs]
Yes

1129
01:33:36,767 --> 01:33:39,067
My brother always drank
too much

1130
01:33:42,076 --> 01:33:43,897
He was sad...

1131
01:33:46,491 --> 01:33:48,562
the saddest of us all

1132
01:33:50,649 --> 01:33:52,471
He needed so much

1133
01:33:55,000 --> 01:33:56,854
and had so little

